HEADWORD: Dicrotic
<hw>Di*crot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ = <?/ to
knock, beat.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of or
pertaining to dicrotism; <as>as, a <ex>dicrotic</ex> pulse</as>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to the second expansion of the artery
